                <note rend="inline" type="source">702.1211 Laredo/42b: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Chargé in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-01-10T11:00:00-05:00"
                            >January 10, 1930—11 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>8. For Clark. Situation at Laredo worse. Several of the banks seem affected. The
                    last thing we want to do is to bother you while you are working but I do want
                    you to know there is a really bad economic situation there.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cotton</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
